BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. (A) The legislative Long-term Care Workforce 3
Study Commission is established. The Commission shall do all of 4
the following: 5
(1) Study the direct care and long-term care workforce in 6
this state and make policy recommendations in each of the 7
following areas: 8
(a) Measuring current demand for direct care workers and 9
projecting future needs of that workforce; 10
(b) Developing a campaign and statewide recruitment 11
strategies to encourage people to join the facility-based and 12
home and community-based long-term care workforce; 13
(c) Supporting career ladders throughout various long-term 14
care settings; 15
(d) Identifying educational needs and methods to fill 16

