program to provide contributions to the postsecondary education 18
of long-term care direct care workers in related fields; 19
(e) Identifying barriers to hiring direct care workers and 20
methods to overcome those barriers; 21
(f) Developing strategies to improve the quality of long- 22
term care jobs; 23
(g) Increasing opportunities for shared staffing among 24
long-term care providers; 25
(h) Recommendations on funding mechanisms, and 26
establishing pilot programs regarding the direct care workforce, 27
such as to pool hours worked by part-time home care workers with 28
the purpose of providing greater employment opportunity and 29
access to employee benefits, or to provide postsecondary 30
education in relevant fields for direct care workers. 31
(2) Not later than August 31, 2027, issue a report of its 32
findings and recommendations to the General Assembly in 33
accordance with section 101.68 of the Revised Code. In producing 34
the report, the Commission shall hear testimony from interested 35
parties and shall provide a public comment period for the draft 36
report language. 37
